Cell.Text: Our chief is weakened. He will not rest, will not sleep. He suffers, and so the tribe suffers. | Yamarz is proud, and refuses to see that we need outside help. | He needs someone to confide in. If it will not be one of us, perhaps it will be you. Go to him.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20AtubQuestion1Topic: What sort of help do you need?

Cell.Text: I am the one cursed by Malacath. It is my burden. I bear it, and continue to lead, and the others see how strong I am. That is how I rule.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzFollowUpB1: You have to do this yourself?

Cell.Text: Hrmph. Breaking a curse is not a simple thing. It is dangerous. | But... To have won against Malacath himself... That would be seen as real power.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzFollowUpC1: A truly strong chief would break the curse, not suffer it.

Cell.Text: [S] You persist? Fine. You go tell Malacath to lift this curse from me. See how well he listens to you. | Offer yourself up as a sacrifice while you're there.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzFollowUpD1: So use me to help you break this curse.

Cell.Text: Are you blind, or just stupid? You think the tribe has not seen you talking to me? You think they would not know? | Do not mistake our life for one of stupidity. It would be the last mistake you make.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzFollowUpB2: I could help you in secret.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Perhaps... Perhaps it might. If nothing else, you could be an excellent sacrifice to Malacath. | You really want to help? You go offer yourself at Malacath's Shrine. Petition him for help. | He might not devour you whole.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzFollowUpC2: Having an outsider do your bidding might seem powerful.

Cell.Text: Spirits! Ghosts! I am cursed, haunted, and I can do nothing. Can you fix that? | Of course you cannot. No one can. It is my lot as Chief of this tribe, and so I suffer quietly.
[S] You? An outsider? I'd sooner slit my own throat than accept help from you. | To even consider it would be such a sign of weakness that I might as well abandon my tribe now.

Node.Caption: DA06Stage20YamarzResponse1: There must be something I can do.

Cell.Text: The kind that curse you, haunt you in the dead of night. There is nothing you can do, nothing anyone can do. | Shagrol, once the leader of this tribe, unhappy with his demise, has dealt with Malacath himself to curse me, curse us all.
S|Atub! Meddlesome woman... You would help us? Help me? | Tell me, outsider. Can you banish spirits? For that is what I need.
